title: [Epidemiology] Covid-19: Infections fell by 65% after first dose of AstraZeneca or Pfizer vaccine, data shows. Researchers also found no evidence that the AstraZeneca and Pfizer vaccines differed in their ability to reduce infection rates (P>0.9), despite them leading to slightly different immune responses.
[Biology] Vaccine Breakthrough Infections with SARS-CoV-2 Variants | NEJM
